# Tabs

Tabs separate related content into different views so users can easily access the related content without refreshing the page.

When a user selects a tab, the related content appears. That content is unique and independent from what appears when the user selects other tabs.

**Variations:** Selected, Hover, Tab Focus, Tab Focus + Selected.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/tabs
```

```tsx
import { Tabs } from '@ids-ts/tabs';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `children` | `React.ReactElement | null | Array<React.ReactEl...` | Yes | Tab contents that need to be displayed |
| `isAutoSelected` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `isHorizontalRuleVisible` | `boolean` | No | Flag to set if horizontal rule is visible |
| `selected` | `string` | Yes | Default tab that should be displayed as active. |
| `alignment` | `'left' | 'center'` | No | How the tabs are aligned |
| `mountOnSelect` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `onChange` | `(id: string) => void` | Yes | onChange callback to trigger actions when changing Tabs. |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface TabsProps extends Omit<Themeable, 'onChange'> {
  /** Tab contents that need to be displayed */
  children: React.ReactElement | null | Array<React.ReactElement | null>;
  /**
   * Flag to set if tab panel is rendered automatically on focus.
   * If false, the tab panel will never be focusable
   *
   * @default true
   */
  isAutoSelected?: boolean;
  /** Flag to set if horizontal rule is visible */
  isHorizontalRuleVisible?: boolean;
  /** Default tab that should be displayed as active. */
  selected: string;
  /** How the tabs are aligned */
  alignment?: 'left' | 'center';
  /** Only mount Tab content once the tab is selected - when false, mount on load and never unmount
   *
   * @default true
   */
  mountOnSelect?: boolean;
  /** onChange callback to trigger actions when changing Tabs. */
  onChange: (id: string) => void;
}
```

</details>

